Python Nativization Algorithm
=============================

BY              Zhean Robby (zrygan) Ganituen
EMAIL           zr.<last name; no vowels>@gmail.com
LAST UPDATE     December 12, 2025

Original toy nativization algorithm written in Python. By Clarence Ang,
Zhean Ganituen, Roan Campo, Clive Ang, and Nathaniel Oco, as a final
course project for Natural Language Processing by Nathaniel Oco at De
La Salle University, Term 1 Academic Year 2025-2026.

Important Notes
---------------

This work is very unfinished and a simple toy algorithm that shows it
is possible to model phonetic nativization rules by the Komisyon sa
Wikang Filipino as a deterministic/rule-based algorithm.

This project is being continued as the `TagaBaybay` project
(<https://github.com/Mango-Cats/TagaBaybay/>) (which, as of writing this,
is also a work-in-progress). This project is currently being spearheaded
by Zhean Ganituen, part of the original project and a member of an
undergraduate thesis group being advised by Nathaniel Oco.

I suggest you look at that project instead

Essential Literature
--------------------

Those interested in this work is advised to check the TagaBayBay project.
The literature we use for this project is the Manwal sa Masinop na Pagsulat
by the Komisyon sa Wikang Filipino.

    https://kwf.gov.ph/wp-content/uploads/MMP_Full.pdf
    (this text is written in Filipino, you can message to help find an
    alternative in English)

The techniques we use here is similar to methodology Zhean et al. used
for their grammar checking project for Tagalog and Bikol

    (publication is forthcoming, for now see)
    [1] https://github.com/zrygan/LanguageTool-Case-Study
    [2] https://github.com/zrygan/Tagalog-and-Bikol-Case-Study
